│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs due to an out-of-bounds access on a SmallVector when         │
│ indexing Entries[Pair.first] in BoUpSLP::isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry. │
│ This indicates that Pair.first contains an index that is not valid for the    │
│ current Entries vector.                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The debug log shows the crash in isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry during   │
│ mask construction for shuffled gathers. The code remaps EntryLanes'           │
│ Pair.first (which denotes the source entry index for each lane) based on      │
│ which entries are used (UsedIdxs) and builds TempEntries accordingly. The     │
│ crash stack points at Entries[Pair.first]->Scalars and                        │
│ Entries[Pair.first]->findLaneForValue, so Pair.first was not properly         │
│ remapped to the new compacted Entries index space.                            │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ EntryLanes stores Pair.first values that come from UsedValuesEntry, which     │
│ refer to indices in a broader space than the local Entries vector. The        │
│ current code attempts to remap Pair.first by looping I over 0..Entries.size() │
│ and replacing Pair.first when it equals I. However, Entries has already been  │
│ filtered to only those indices for which UsedIdxs.test(I) is true. If         │
│ Pair.first refers to an original index that is not within 0..Entries.size()-1 │
│ (because Entries is a subset and uses dense 0..N-1 now), the equality         │
│ comparison will never trigger, leaving Pair.first pointing to an invalid      │
│ index. Subsequent access Entries[Pair.first] asserts.                         │
│ In short: The code assumes Pair.first indexes align with the current Entries  │
│ indices and tries to update them via equality, but Pair.first encodes         │
│ original indices from the broader UsedValuesEntry mapping. When Entries is    │
│ compacted, Pair.first must be updated via a proper mapping from original      │
│ indices to new compact indices. The current loop does not build or use such a │
│ mapping, hence the out-of-range index and assertion.                          │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - Edit Point 1 (lines 14671-14683 in                                          │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp): Replace the ad-hoc          │
│ Pair.first remapping with a robust map from original entry indices to         │
│ compacted indices. Build DenseMap<unsigned, unsigned> OldToNew during         │
│ TempEntries construction, then remap all Pair.first using this map. Also drop │
│ any EntryLanes whose Pair.first is not present in OldToNew (defensive).       │
│                                                                               │
│ New code block suggestion:                                                    │
│   // Iterate through all shuffled scalars and select entries, which can be    │
│ used                                                                          │
│   // for final shuffle.                                                       │
│   SmallVector<const TreeEntry *> TempEntries;                                 │
│   DenseMap<unsigned, unsigned> OldToNew;                                      │
│   for (unsigned I = 0, Sz = Entries.size(); I < Sz; ++I) {                    │
│     if (!UsedIdxs.test(I))                                                    │
│       continue;                                                               │
│     unsigned NewIdx = TempEntries.size();                                     │
│     OldToNew.try_emplace(I, NewIdx);                                          │
│     TempEntries.push_back(Entries[I]);                                        │
│   }                                                                           │
│   Entries.swap(TempEntries);                                                  │
│   // Remap lanes to the new compacted Entries indexing.                       │
│   for (std::pair<unsigned, int> &Pair : EntryLanes) {                         │
│     auto ItMap = OldToNew.find(Pair.first);                                   │
│     if (ItMap == OldToNew.end())                                              │
│       continue; // Lane refers to an entry we did not select; keep as-is      │
│ (will be ignored later).                                                      │
│     Pair.first = ItMap->second;                                               │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit Point 2 (narrow fix within lines 14678-14681): Remove the existing     │
│ loop that remaps Pair.first by comparing to I (which is incorrect after       │
│ compaction). This prevents stale indices from persisting.                     │
│                                                                               │
│ These changes ensure Entries[Pair.first] always indexes within                │
│ Entries.size(), or the lane is skipped by subsequent logic when               │
│ Entries.empty() or lanes mismatch.                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By introducing an explicit mapping from original entry indices to the         │
│ compacted Entries indices and using it to remap EntryLanes, we avoid          │
│ out-of-bounds access in Entries[Pair.first]. This fixes the assertion and     │
│ aligns the mask construction logic with the filtered Entries subset, making   │
│ isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry robust against index space changes during │
│ compaction.                                                                   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
│                                                                               │
