  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs due to an
out-of-bounds access on a SmallVector when indexing Entries[Pair.first] in
BoUpSLP::isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry. This indicates that Pair.first
contains an index that is not valid for the current Entries vector.\n\n2.
Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows the crash in
isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry during mask construction for shuffled
gathers. The code remaps EntryLanes' Pair.first (which denotes the source entry
index for each lane) based on which entries are used (UsedIdxs) and builds
TempEntries accordingly. The crash stack points at Entries[Pair.first]->Scalars
and Entries[Pair.first]->findLaneForValue, so Pair.first was not properly
remapped to the new compacted Entries index space.\n\n3. Root Cause
Analysis:\nEntryLanes stores Pair.first values that come from UsedValuesEntry,
which refer to indices in a broader space than the local Entries vector. The
current code attempts to remap Pair.first by looping I over 0..Entries.size() and
replacing Pair.first when it equals I. However, Entries has already been filtered
to only those indices for which UsedIdxs.test(I) is true. If Pair.first refers to
an original index that is not within 0..Entries.size()-1 (because Entries is a
subset and uses dense 0..N-1 now), the equality comparison will never trigger,
leaving Pair.first pointing to an invalid index. Subsequent access
Entries[Pair.first] asserts.\nIn short: The code assumes Pair.first indexes align
with the current Entries indices and tries to update them via equality, but
Pair.first encodes original indices from the broader UsedValuesEntry mapping.
When Entries is compacted, Pair.first must be updated via a proper mapping from
original indices to new compact indices. The current loop does not build or use
such a mapping, hence the out-of-range index and assertion.\n\n4. Proposed Edit
Point(s):\n- Edit Point 1 (lines 14671-14683 in
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp): Replace the ad-hoc Pair.first
remapping with a robust map from original entry indices to compacted indices.
Build DenseMap<unsigned, unsigned> OldToNew during TempEntries construction, then
remap all Pair.first using this map. Also drop any EntryLanes whose Pair.first is
not present in OldToNew (defensive).\n\nNew code block suggestion:\n  // Iterate
through all shuffled scalars and select entries, which can be used\n  // for
final shuffle.\n  SmallVector<const TreeEntry *> TempEntries;\n
DenseMap<unsigned, unsigned> OldToNew;\n  for (unsigned I = 0, Sz =
Entries.size(); I < Sz; ++I) {\n    if (!UsedIdxs.test(I))\n      continue;\n
unsigned NewIdx = TempEntries.size();\n    OldToNew.try_emplace(I, NewIdx);\n
TempEntries.push_back(Entries[I]);\n  }\n  Entries.swap(TempEntries);\n  // Remap
lanes to the new compacted Entries indexing.\n  for (std::pair<unsigned, int>
&Pair : EntryLanes) {\n    auto ItMap = OldToNew.find(Pair.first);\n    if (ItMap
== OldToNew.end())\n      continue; // Lane refers to an entry we did not select;
keep as-is (will be ignored later).\n    Pair.first = ItMap->second;\n  }\n\n-
Edit Point 2 (narrow fix within lines 14678-14681): Remove the existing loop that
remaps Pair.first by comparing to I (which is incorrect after compaction). This
prevents stale indices from persisting.\n\nThese changes ensure
Entries[Pair.first] always indexes within Entries.size(), or the lane is skipped
by subsequent logic when Entries.empty() or lanes mismatch.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy
introducing an explicit mapping from original entry indices to the compacted
Entries indices and using it to remap EntryLanes, we avoid out-of-bounds access
in Entries[Pair.first]. This fixes the assertion and aligns the mask construction
logic with the filtered Entries subset, making
isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry robust against index space changes during
compaction.",
